json.text: Hey everyone, it's your girl Jenn and today I am back with 'What Would Jenn Wear'
which is a segment where you tweet me your fashion dilemma
and I try my best to answer them and I know it's been a hot minute since I filmed one of these
but we're officially back, so let's get started with our first question
Nini tweets
Ok, so unfortunately you've been friend-zoned but the good news is
you're going on some sort of outing with him or her and I think that's a start
I specifically bought this shirt just to show you what I would wear for this outfit
Here I have a casual jeans and tee combo that you can really rock anywhere
but if you look closely you can see some subtle messaging here
hint, hint
Hopefully your crush will see it. I've tied a little not on this tee since it's huge
and then elongated the look with some navy skinnies
I popped on some mules out of convenience and then added this adorable little star choker
because you're a star and hopefully the date goes well
let me know how it goes
Jeanette asks
So a no-brainer way to rock your summer jeans into the fall is simply by adding some dark colors
I know groundbreaking. I paired my blue distressed jeans with the black trench
It instantly makes it moody and great for autumn and winter
To make this a little bit more casual I popped on a black cropped hoodie
I accessorized with some gold jewelry and then added a dark lip just to vamp it up
for shoes, I slipped into some Navy mules to bring out the blue in the denim
and I know it's a fashion faux pas to mix navy and black together but honestly screw the rules
wear whatever you think looks best and I think navy and black are perfectly acceptable together
The next tweet comes from, Mara. She asks
First off I just want to congratulate you on being a senior in college
college is really tough and so the fact that you're on your last year makes me really proud of you
You go girl
Now here's your outfit.
I wanted something really casual and comfy for college
this is a really nice soft flannel top and I like this silhouette because
it's more of a blouse rather than just your normal standard flannel
For shorts, I have these nice stretchy ones from 'The Fifth Label'
anything with an elastic waistband is going to keep your body happy and comfy
I threw on an olive beanie to add a pop of color
and then more this statement necklace piece for some edge
lastly stomp around in some classic ankle boots and if heels aren't your thing
definitely just wear normal boots that you find comfortable
actually just wear whatever comfortable shoes that you own
I mean these outfits are just meant for a source of inspiration
I also have a 'Back to College' lookbook that I made maybe like two weeks ago
so if you haven't seen that video feel free to click here, I have a lot of great outfits
that I would have rocked school. I know some of the comments were like
who wears that to school blah blah
but honestly I like legitimately wore thigh-high boots to school
It was my way to express myself everyday and honestly I feel like
I came up with some pretty daring outfits to school because
I just loved getting dressed in the morning and please don't judge people for wearing certain things to school
I feel like that really blocks people's confidence
to wear whatever they like
and once you stop judging what other people are wearing
you can start being more free with your own style
wow I don't know how I got into that tangent but ok let's move on to the next question
This question comes from, Adri. She asks
alright so this is my attempt at business casual with the twist
This looks like a dress but it's actually two pieces
On the top I have this patterned white button down. The short sleeves make it casual
but the structure of it still makes it formal. On the bottom I have this beige Searsucker skirt
in this really interesting cut. I really like the fact that you can show a tiny bit of your leg in the middle
but the outer layers cover you up
I slid into some nude suede flat mules and then accessorized some gold jewelry
Personally I think that this would totally work in a business setting maybe
In more of a creative field but then again I've never had to work in an with a strict dress code
Modify what you have to. So I hope it helps
Next up, StSundae asks
This question makes me so happy because I've been there girl
Long distance relationships are tough and I've had to meet Ben at airport for many occasions
So this is an outfit that I would wear if I was trying to do elegant but casual
The elegance factor comes from this colorful printed cover up. It's flowy and comfy and add a touch of romance
Underneath I'm wearing a black bodysuit
and then wore it with some distressed shorts to give it more of an effortless feel
I wore a pop of blue on my shoes and then accessorized with these cute star earrings
and that's it. I hope you and your boyfriend have an amazing time together
I'm routing for you guys
The last question comes from Facebook
Grace, asks
First off, boobs are great whether you're big small and honestly
there's a lot of pros on being small chested. I will discuss those details in a separate video
To help your question in particular. I think a really great way to enhance the chest
is to wear tops with a ruffle detail in combination with a sweetheart shape
Here I have this pin stripe top from Bardot
I believe this top checks both of those boxes. The ruffle gives the illusion of a fuller chest
and the sweet heart shape just defines it
For the bottom I'm wearing a white corduroy skirt and then I popped on some nude platforms
to give me that height that I want.
Accessorize with some cool tone jewelry and voila there's your outfit
Alrighty folks that's all the time I have for today
If you'd like to be featured in the next 'What Would Jenn Wear'
Feel free to tweet me at @imjennim on Twitter
With the hashtag #WWJW
and you might be picked for the next episode
Lastly, before I left I wanted to announce that
This is your last chance to get the 'JennNeSaisQuoi' collection, with Colourpop
This is my collaboration with them and unfortunately this term is up
I signed a three-month contract
The last day you can purchase it is September 13th
So please grab it while you can. It is truly one of my favorite quads
I'm wearing it on my eyes right now it is perfect for the fall
So if you'd like to purchase it feel free to open the description box
I'll put a link in there and you can grab it
Sad
All good things come to an end
Anyway, I hope you guys enjoyed the video
and i'll see you guys in my next one
Bye
